# EXPECT: [P-2]
# Dereferencing a raw pointer can read freed or invalid memory (temporal/spatial
# UB). Under --strict, `.read()` in SAFE code is a hard error — raw pointer access
# is the audited-`unsafe` core's job, exactly like Rust requires `unsafe` to deref
# a `*const T`. (std/core library code is trusted and exempt.)
def main():
    unsafe:
        mut p = alloc[int](1)
        p.write(0, 5)
    mut q = alloc[int](1)      # (also [U-1], but the point is the read below)
    mut v = q.read()           # [P-2]: raw deref outside unsafe
    print(v)
